data.description:
- Multi-stage Dockerfile for a Next.js application using Node.js 22 Alpine
- Build stage:
  - Installs dependencies and builds the Next.js application
- Production stage:
  - Creates secure user/group for running the application
  - Copies only necessary files from build stage (built app, modules, public assets)
  - Exposes port 3000 for web traffic
  - Setup for production-ready Node.js application with minimal image size and security best practices
- Available to be used by container orchestration systems and deployment pipelines

- Main README file for Invoify, a web-based invoice generator application
- Key exports/information for other components:
  * Core technology stack: Next.js 13, TypeScript, React, Shadcn UI
  * Available features and functionality for integration
  * Required environment variables (NODEMAILER_EMAIL, NODEMAILER_PW)
  * Installation and setup instructions
  * Future roadmap features for planning
  * Compatibility notice regarding Firefox browser issues
  * License information (MIT)
The README serves as the primary documentation source for:
- Project overview and capabilities
- Technical requirements and dependencies
- Development setup process
- External integrations (email functionality)
- Current limitations and planned features

- A Next.js catch-all route handler (`[...rest]`) that handles any undefined routes
- Immediately triggers Next.js' built-in 404 Not Found page using `notFound()`
- Used for internationalization routes (`[locale]`) that don't match any defined paths
- Exports a default page component that other files don't need to import/use
- Serves as a fallback route handler for the application's routing system

- Root layout component for a Next.js application with internationalization support
- Exports metadata configuration for SEO optimization and site information
- Provides essential structure wrapping all pages with:
  - Next-intl for internationalization
  - Vercel Analytics integration
  - Global providers for state management
  - Base navigation and footer components
  - Toast notifications
  - Custom fonts configuration
- Handles locale-based routing and message loading
- Implements structured data (JSON-LD) for SEO
- Configures base styling with Tailwind CSS and custom font classes

- Main page component for the root route ('/') of the application
- Wraps the InvoiceMain component in a main element with padding and container styling
- Imports and uses InvoiceMain component from the components directory
- Serves as the entry point for the invoice management interface
- Uses Next.js App Router format with locale support in the URL structure
- Exports a single default component for use as a page in Next.js routing

- Template viewer component that dynamically loads invoice templates based on URL parameter
- Exports a Next.js page component for viewing invoice templates at route `/[locale]/template/[id]`
- Uses dynamic imports to load specific invoice template components based on template number
- Accesses form data from parent context using React Hook Form
- Renders the selected template with sender, receiver, and details data from form values
- Other files can import this as a page component but it's primarily used by Next.js routing system
- Serves as a preview page for different invoice template designs

- API endpoint handler for exporting invoices using Next.js route handlers
- Exposes a single POST method that processes invoice export requests
- Delegates actual export functionality to the `exportInvoiceService`
- Acts as a bridge between client-side requests and server-side invoice export logic
- Can be accessed by frontend components through `/api/invoice/export` endpoint

data.dockerfile:
FROM node:16-alpine
ENV NODE_ENV=development
ENV BABEL_ENV=development
WORKDIR /app
